# Parallel Execution Agent - Environment Configuration
# ==============================================================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual API keys
# Never commit .env to version control!
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. cp .env.example .env
# 2. Edit .env with your actual API keys
# 3. source .env (or use direnv)
# 4. Run tests: pytest test_quorum_integration.py
#
# See ../../SECURITY_KEY_ROTATION.md for detailed setup procedures
# ==============================================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Gemini API Key (Quorum Validation)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used by:
#   - quorum_validator.py: Multi-model consensus validation
#   - demo_quorum_integration.py: Quorum demonstrations
#   - test_quorum_integration.py: Quorum integration tests
#
# Get your key: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# Required API: Generative Language API
# Model Access: gemini-1.5-flash, gemini-1.5-pro, gemini-2.5-flash, gemini-2.5-pro
#
# Rate Limits (as of 2025-10):
#   - Gemini Flash: 15 requests/minute (free tier)
#   - Gemini Pro: 2 requests/minute (free tier)
#   - Paid tiers: Higher limits available
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google API Key (Pydantic AI Integration)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used by: Pydantic AI integrations requiring Google models
# Note: Should be the same value as GEMINI_API_KEY for compatibility
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key_here

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Z.ai API Key (GLM Models for Quorum)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used by:
#   - quorum_validator.py: GLM model validation in consensus
#   - Multi-model quorum validation requiring GLM models
#
# Get your key: https://z.ai/dashboard
# Model Access: GLM-4.5-Air, GLM-4.5, GLM-4.6
#
# Rate Limits:
#   - GLM-4.5-Air (Haiku equiv): 5 concurrent requests
#   - GLM-4.5 (Sonnet equiv): 20 concurrent requests
#   - GLM-4.6 (Opus equiv): 10 concurrent requests
#   - Total concurrent capacity: 35 requests
ZAI_API_KEY=your_zai_api_key_here

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Testing Configuration
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Quorum validation tests require both GEMINI_API_KEY and ZAI_API_KEY
# Tests will skip if keys are not set
#
# Run tests:
#   pytest test_quorum_integration.py -v
#   python demo_quorum_integration.py
#
# Minimum requirements for testing:
#   - GEMINI_API_KEY: Required (will fail if missing)
#   - ZAI_API_KEY: Required (will fail if missing)
#   - Ollama models: Optional (tests will skip if unavailable)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Security Notes
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. This .env file is excluded by .gitignore - verify before committing
# 2. Keys provide full API access - treat as passwords
# 3. Rotate keys regularly (every 30-90 days recommended)
# 4. Use separate keys for dev/staging/production
# 5. Enable IP restrictions in provider dashboards when possible
# 6. Monitor usage for anomalies in provider dashboards
#
# See ../../SECURITY_KEY_ROTATION.md for:
# - API key rotation procedures
# - Testing new keys
# - Emergency response plan
# - Security best practices
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
